<body>

   <h1>🌠Puskas Award</h1>

<div class="section">
<h2> What is the Puskas Award?</h2>
<p>
The <strong>FIFA Puskas Award</strong> is an annual honor given to the player (male or female) who is judged to have scored the <strong>most aesthetically significant and beautiful goal of the year</strong>. The award was established in <strong>2009</strong> by FIFA in honor of <strong>Ferenc Puskás</strong>, the legendary Hungarian striker known for his incredible goal-scoring ability and technical brilliance.
</p>
</div>

<div class="section">
<h2>📌 Key Facts</h2>
<ul>
<li>📅<strong>Interception: </strong>2009</li>
<li>&#128100<strong>Named After: </strong>Ferenc Puskas, Hungary and Real Madrid legend
<li>🏆<strong>Presented By: </strong> FIFA(<em>Federation Internationale de Football Association</em>)</li>
<li>🌐<strong>Eligibility: </strong>Open to professional footballers of all genders, from any league or competition recognized by FIFA</li>
<li>🧠<strong>Judging Criteria:</strong>
<ul>
        <li>Aesthetic quality of the goal</li>
        <li>Importance of the match</li>
        <li>Absence of luck or mistakes from the opposing team</li>
        <li>Fair play (the goal-scorer must not have committed a foul in the lead-up)</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>
</div>

<div class="section voting-process">
🗳️<strong>Voting-Process:</strong>
<p>Initially, fans voted online from a shortlist of nominated goals. In more recent years, voting is combined between <strong>fans and FIFA-appointed experts</strong> to determine the winner.</p>
</div>
<div class="section">
<h2>🥇 Notable Winners</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>Cristiano Ronaldo</strong> (2009)-for a long-range strike with Manchester United</li>
    <li><strong>Neymar</strong> (2011)-for a stunning solo goal with Santos</li>
    <li><strong>Mohamed Salah</strong> (2018)-for a curling strike in the Merseyside derby</li>
    <li><strong>Son Heung-min</strong> (2020)-for a solo run goal with Tottenham Hotspur</li>
  </ul>
</div>

